ntal Lives of the Artists, in particular how style was understood to register an artist’s encounter with place. Through new readings of critical ideas, long-standing regional prejudices, and entire biographies, The Traveling Artist in the Italian Renaissance provides a groundbreaking case for the significance of mobility in the interpretation of art and the wider discipline of art history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArt, Italiany16th century. 0aArt, Italiany16th century.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh00010129. 0aArt, RenaissancezItaly. 0aArt, RenaissancezItaly.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85007865. 0aArtistsxTravelzItalyxHistoryy16th century. 7aART / History / Renaissance.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030019867640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021224240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300212242423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300212242/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY